\begin_layout Paragraph
The Pietra coefficient.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This summary statistic of the Lorenz curve is defined as the largest gap
 between 
\begin_inset Formula $L(p)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
P_{L}=\max_{0\le p\le1}\left\{ p-L(p)\right\} 
\end{equation}

\end_inset

also written as 
